It is with great sadness that AUSI announces the abrupt death of our beloved brother *Kabuubi* *Salman*, 5th year Law Student from SOA University Bhubaneswar Odisha State... who was also part of the AUSI constitutional assembly.

He suffered a cardiac arrest(reportedly) and was rushed to the hospital where he has been confirmed dead today at 2:36pm at Sum Hospital Bhubaneswar..(private hospital)

At this moment his body has been transferred to the a government hospital (since it’s an international case) where post-mortem is to be taken. And statements are being taken by police from the immediate witnesses.

The university says they are holding a meeting to plan on the most appropriate way of his transportation back home and arrangements for his dismissal. 

Further details are to be communicated and incase any assistance is needed you shall still be informed. 

As of now we pray that may the almighty God strength his family and friends. And may his soul rest in eternal peace 🕊️🕊️🕊️

*SUBJECT: Invitation to Online Webinar*
We are delighted to extend our warmest invitation to you to join us for an engaging and informative online interactive session via Google Meet. This session aims to provide you with valuable insights into our institution, academic programs, admission process, scholarships and everything you need to know about studying with us at GJIMT.

Date: 5th July,2024 Time:  3:00pm IST Platform: Google Meet 

*NB: Kindly confirm as per your country timing...*
```Ghana & Liberia time 9:30am, Nigeria & Morocco 10:30am, South Africa, Zimbabwe & South Sudan 11:30am and Tanzania & Egypt 12:30pm.
During this session, you will have the opportunity to``` :

   1.Learn about our diverse range of academic programs tailored to meet global standards.
2. Scholarship at GJIMT
3. Gain insights into the vibrant campus life and student community.
4. Interact with faculty members and current international students to hear firsthand experiences.
5. Understand the admission requirements, application process, and available scholarships for international students.
6. Get answers to all your queries about studying abroad and transitioning to a new academic environment.
To register for this exclusive session, please fill out the registration form at https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdNiWyR2XLDU3RltqA4nF3YIt9pfnx8AIBK-iWqJ0NGnQS6ew/viewform?usp=pp_url

We understand that choosing the right educational institution is a significant decision, and we are committed to providing you with all the necessary information to make an informed choice. Whether you're considering undergraduate, graduate, or research programs, this session will serve as a valuable resource in your decision-making process.
Don't miss this opportunity to connect with us and embark on an exciting journey towards academic excellence and personal growth.

Should you have any questions or require further assistance, please feel free to contact or WhatsApp at +91 6283 367 760 or email at gjimt.internationaladmissions@gmail.com .

RULES AND REGULATIONS

1. ALL PLAYERS MUST BE ON THE TRAINING AND MATCH FIELD ON TIME BY 6:30 PM.

2. ALL PLAYERS MUST WEAR APPROPRIATE SPORTS GEAR AT ALL TIMES, INCLUDING SHIRTS, SHORTS, SOCKS, GLOVES, AND SHOES.

3. NO FORM OF VERBAL OR PHYSICAL ALTERCATION, ASSAULT, OR ABUSIVE LANGUAGE IS PERMITTED ON THE FIELD.

4. ANY INDIVIDUAL FOUND VIOLATING RULE 3 WILL BE IMMEDIATELY REMOVED FROM THE GAME.

5. ALL GRIEVANCES MUST BE REPORTED TO THE MANAGERS OR CAPTAINS PRESENT ON THE FIELD FOR RESOLUTION.

7. ANY PLAYER WHO IS ABSENT FOR THREE TRAINING SESSIONS WILL NOT BE ELIGIBLE TO PARTICIPATE IN THE NEXT MATCH.

THANK YOU FOR YOUR COOPERATION.

PLEASE READ AND ACCEPT THESE RULES AND REGULATIONS.

1. ALL PLAYERS MUST BE ON THE TRAINING AND MATCH FIELD ON TIME BY 3:30 PM.

11/11/24, 8:32 AM - Alagie KIIT: AFCON tournament began in 2023, it's a dynamic event designed to bring together international students through the shared passion for football. This tournament mirrors the prestigious Africa Cup of Nations, creating a competitive yet friendly atmosphere where teams representing different groups or countries compete for victory. 

The event emphasizes inclusivity, teamwork, and cultural exchange, allowing participants to showcase their skills and foster camaraderie among peers. It features group stages leading to knockout rounds, with matches adhering to well-structured rules. The tournament not only highlights the spirit of competition but also serves as a platform for building connections, promoting unity, and celebrating diversity within the international student community.

11/12/24, 11:04 PM - Alagie KIIT: AFCON tournament began in 2023, it's a dynamic event designed to bring together international students through the shared passion for football. This tournament mirrors the prestigious Africa Cup of Nations, creating a competitive yet friendly atmosphere where teams representing different groups or countries compete for victory. 

The event emphasizes inclusivity, teamwork, and cultural exchange, allowing participants to showcase their skills and foster camaraderie among peers. It features group stages leading to knockout rounds, with matches adhering to well-structured rules. The tournament not only highlights the spirit of competition but also serves as a platform for building connections, promoting unity, and celebrating diversity within the international student community.

12/18/24, 11:47 PM - Alagie KIIT: Dear Ballers,

I hope this message finds you well. I’m writing to address a matter of importance in light of recent events at our neighboring university, SOA. It is deeply disheartening to hear about such incidents, particularly involving our fellow African brothers.

Let us take a moment to reflect on why we are here. We have left our homes, traveled thousands of miles, and are pursuing our education in a foreign land. Our loved ones back home constantly worry about the challenges we face as students, living far away without immediate family support. In such situations, our friends, our brothers become our chosen family.

I want to remind everyone to stay focused on what brought us here: our education, our goals, and our future. Let us ensure that our actions reflect positively on ourselves and our communities. Engage in activities that build us up and uphold our values, while being mindful not to engage in anything that could harm us or others.

Remember, we are ambassadors of our countries, and our actions speak volumes about the character of our communities. Let’s continue to support each other, remain focused on our academic and personal growth, and work towards the success that we all aspire to achieve.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation.

Regards,
Alagie Madi Ceesay
